%% Ingestion Architecture & State Flow

%% This diagram details the critical boundary layer between external monitoring
%% infrastructure and the AutoResolve internal event bus. It maps the exact
%% lifecycle of an incoming alert webhook, highlighting how the system ensures
%% data integrity and high availability before the AI agents are ever invoked.

%% Key Mechanisms Illustrated:
%% - Webhook Reception: The flow begins when Prometheus Alertmanager sends an
%%   alert payload via a POST request to the FastAPI Gateway.
%% - Strict Schema Validation: Before any processing occurs, the payload is
%%   intercepted by a Pydantic Guardrail. If the alert is malformed or missing
%%   required fields, the gateway immediately rejects it with a 422 Unprocessable
%%   Entity error, protecting downstream systems from invalid state.
%% - Asynchronous Handoff: Validated payloads are passed to the AIOKafkaProducer,
%%   which publishes the event to the incidents Kafka topic. Once successfully
%%   published, the gateway immediately returns a 202 Accepted response to
%%   Prometheus, decoupling the fast ingestion path from the slower LLM reasoning
%%   process.
%% - Resilience & Fallback: If the Kafka broker is unavailable, the gateway
%%   gracefully catches the failure and returns a 503 Service Unavailable. This
%%   explicit error code signals Alertmanager (or the on-call routing system like
%%   PagerDuty) to bypass AutoResolve and fall back to alerting a human engineer
%%   directly.

graph TD
    P[Prometheus Alertmanager] -->|POST /webhook| F[FastAPI Gateway]
    
    subgraph FastAPI Runtime
        F -->|Validate| S[Pydantic Guardrail]
        S -->|Validation Error| R422[422 Unprocessable Entity]
        S -->|Pass| K_Prod[AIOKafkaProducer]
    end
    
    K_Prod -->|Publish Event| Topic[(Kafka Topic: 'incidents')]
    Topic -.->|Consumed by| LangGraph[LangGraph Agent Swarm]
    K_Prod -->|Success| R202[202 Accepted]
    
    %% Fallback
    K_Prod -->|Broker Down| R503[503 Service Unavailable -> Fallback to Human]